    <div class="row section-alt">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="col-sm-7">
          <h3>Identifying a Beta Exam</h3>
          <ul class="blue-chevron">
            <li>Oracle Certification Beta Exam numbers begin with "1Z1"; Oracle Certification Production Exam numbers begin with "1Z0". Both versions of the exam have the same suffix. <br>
              <br>
              For example, a beta version of an exam may be 1Z1-512. The production version of this exam will be 1Z0-512.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
