<div id="page-cert-course-submission"> 
<div class="container-fluid bc-1">
      <div class="container">
        <ol class="breadcrumb">
  <li><a href="/home">Home</a></li>
<li>Course Submission Form</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
</div>
  <!-- Course Banner Title Section -->
  <section class="cw22-bg6">
    <div class="cc-banner-single x-small bnnr-cert-course-submission">
      <div class="container">
      <div class="caption">
          <h1> <span class="pagetitlebrand">Oracle</span> <span>Certification</span></h1>
          <h2>Course Submission Form</h2>
        </div>
        </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <!--Overview-->
  <section id="course-submission-overview" class="section-content">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="row"> 
        <!-- Overview -->
        <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-7 col-md-7">
          <h3 class="overview-title">What is the Course Submission Form?</strong></h3>
          <p>The Course Submission Form is a tool for certification candidates to submit their required training details for verification. This form is required in order to obtain most Oracle Certified Professional and Oracle Certified Master certifications as well as some Expert Program certifications. Completing the Course Submission Form will accomplish two tasks related to your certification:</p>
          <ul class="blue-chevron">
            <li>It will trigger a request for Oracle to verify your attendance in an approved hands-on Course.</li>
            <li>After your attendance has been verified by Oracle, the form will generate a permanent record in Oracle's certification database, showing that you have met the requirement.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="col-xs-10 col-sm-5 col-md-5"><img class="img-responsive hidden-xs" alt="The Course Submission Form" src="/file/collections/course-submission1.jpg"></div>
      </div>
      <!--row--> 
    </div>
  </section>
  <style>
  #course-submission-content {background-color: #f8f8f8;}
  #course-submission-content .well{background-color: #fff;}
  #course-submission-menu{margin-bottom:30px;}
  </style>
  <!--Releases Menu-->
  <section id="course-submission-content" class="section-content">
    <div class="container">
    <!--Tab Menu-->
      <div class="row id="course-submission-content"">
        <div class="col-lg-1"></div>
        <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-12 col-lg-10">
          <ul id="course-submission-menu" class="nav nav-pills nav-training nav-justified">
            <li class="active"><a class="tab-lead" href="#tab-1" data-toggle="tab">Who should submit the form?</a></li>
            <li><a href="#tab-2" data-toggle="tab">What are the course requirements?</a></li>
            <li><a href="#tab-3" data-toggle="tab">How do I submit the form?</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="col-lg-1"></div>
      </div>
      <!--row--> 
      <!--Tab Content-->
      <div class="row">
        <div class="content-wrapper">
          <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-12 col-lg-12">
            <div id="course-submission-tabcontent" class="tab-content" > 
              <!--Who should not submit it?-->
              <div class="tab-pane fade in active" id="tab-1">
                <div class="row">
                  <div class="col-md-12">
                    <div class="well well-lg">
                      <h3 class="ocom-heading">Who should submit the form?</h3>
                      <hr />
                      <h4><strong>Who should submit the form?</strong></h4>
                      <ul class="blue-chevron">
                        <li>
                        All candidates pursuing an Oracle Certified Professional, Oracle Certified Master or Expert certification path, which requires training, who have attended the approved hands-on course.
                        <ul>
                          <li> Candidates completing a path that requires more than one course should complete a Course Submission Form for each course that they have completed.</li>
                          <li>OCM candidates should submit 3 forms, one for each required course and the 3rd "shipping form" to provide their size and mailing address to receive the OCM apparel item. The 3rd form is crucial as it triggers processing of the success kit. The 3rd form or "shipping form," is submitted exactly like the course submission form.</li>
                        </ul>
                        </li>
                      </ul>
                      <hr />
                      <h4><strong>Who should not submit it? </strong></h4>
                      <ul class="blue-chevron">
                        <li>Candidates who are upgrading their existing Oracle Certified Professional or Oracle Certified Expert credential from a previous version via the standard upgrade exam(s).</li>
                        <li>Candidates who are required to attend a hands-on course but who have not yet attended it. </li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>
                    <!--well--> 
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <!--What are the course requirements?-->
              <div class="tab-pane fade" id="tab-2">
                <div class="row">
                  <div class="col-md-12">
                    <div class="well well-lg">
						<h3 class="faqs-heading">What are the course requirements?</h3>
						<hr />
						<p>To get certified, you must pass a related certification exam(s). Some certifications require you to take a related training course(s) in addition to passing the exam(s).</p>
						
						<p>If your certification does require training, you can choose from a list of courses included on your certification path page.</p>
						<hr />
						<h4><strong>View courses that fulfill training requirements for the following product certifications:</strong></h4>
						<h5><strong>Database</strong></h5>
						<ul class="blue-chevron">
						<li><a href="/oracle-database-12c-administrator-certified-professional/trackp_249">Oracle Database 12c Administrator Certified Professional</a></li>
						<li><a href="/oracle-database-12c-administrator-certified-master/trackp_462">Oracle Database 12c Administrator Certified Master</a></li>
						<li><a href="/oracle-database-11g-administrator-certified-professional/trackp_289">Oracle Database 11g Administrator Certified Professional</a></li>
						<li><a href="/oracle-database-11g-administrator-certified-master/trackp_52">Oracle Database 11g Administrator Certified Master</a></li>
						<li><a href="/oracle-certified-expert-oracle-real-application-clusters-11g-and-grid-infrastructure-administrator/trackp_207">Oracle Certified Expert, Oracle RAC 11g Release 2 and Grid Infrastructure Administrator</a></li>
						<li><a href="/oracle-certified-expert-oracle-database-12c-rac-and-grid-infrastructure-administrator/trackp_483">Oracle Certified Expert, Oracle Database 12c: RAC and Grid Infrastructure Administration</a></li>
						<li><a href="/oracle-certified-expert-oracle-database-12c-data-guard-administrator/trackp_385">Oracle Certified Expert, Oracle Database 12c: Data Guard Administration</a></li>
						<li><a href="/oracle-database-11g-performance-tuning-certified-expert/trackp_169">Oracle Database 11g Performance Tuning Expert</a></li>
						<li><a href="/oracle-certified-expert-oracle-database-12c-performance-management-and-tuning/trackp_352">Oracle Certified Expert, Oracle Database 12c: Performance Management and Tuning</a></li>
						</ul>
						<h5><strong>Applications</strong></h5>
						<ul class="blue-chevron">
						<li><a href="/siebel-8-consultant-certified-expert/trackp_118">Siebel 8 Consultant Certified Expert</a></li>
						</ul>
						<h5><strong>Java and Middleware</strong></h5>
						<ul class="blue-chevron">
						<li><a href="/oracle-certified-master-java-ee-6-enterprise-architect/trackp_212">Oracle Certified Master, Java EE 6 Enterprise Architect</a></li>
						</ul>
						<h5><strong>Operating Systems</strong></h5>
						<ul class="blue-chevron">
						<li><a href="/oracle-certified-professional-oracle-solaris-11-system-administrator/trackp_190">Oracle Certified Professional, Oracle Solaris 11 System Administrator</a></li>
						</ul>
						</div>
                    <!--well--> 
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <!--How do I submit the form?-->
              <div class="tab-pane fade" id="tab-3">
                <div class="row">
                  <div class="col-md-12">
                    <div class="well well-lg">
                      <h3 class="faqs-heading">How do I submit the form?</h3>
                      <hr />
                      <p>The form may be submitted at any time in your certification path, after you have completed the training requirement. However, you will only receive the certification success kit once all certification requirements have been met. </p>
                      <ul class="blue-chevron">
                        <li>Go to pearsonvue.com/oracle</li>
                        <li>Select Submit Course Form</li>
                        <li>Sign In</li>
                        <li>Select New Submission in the upper right corner of the table</li>
                        <li>Follow the instructions throughout the form: You will need your Oracle Testing ID, Enrollment Number from your OU course (WDP, OA, and Training On Demand students may leave this blank), as well as the dates and location of your course.</li>
                        <li>OCMs and Instructors will need an Authorization Code to complete the form. These codes can be obtained from <a href="https://help-education.oracle.com/pls/apex/f?p=109:1:12437636873395::::p_prod_id,p_org_id,p_lang:3,1001,US">Oracle Certification Support</a></li>
                        <li>Verification of your details may take up to 5 business days. You will receive either an approval email, or an email requesting further information within 5 business days.</li>
                        <li>You should submit only ONE course form for each certification unless you are submitting for an OCM certification.</li>
                      </ul>
                      <hr />
                      <h4><strong>What happens after I submit the form?</strong></h4>
